data.chText: 稳定的；稳固的；牢固的
data.enText: firmly fixed; not likely to move, change or fail

data.chText: 稳定的价格
data.enText: stable prices

data.chText: 稳定的关系
data.enText: a stable relationship

data.chText: 这架梯子好像不太稳。
data.enText: This ladder doesn't seem very stable.

data.chText: 患者病情稳定。
data.enText: The patient's condition is stable (= it is not getting worse) .

data.chText: 稳重的；沉稳的；持重的
data.enText: calm and reasonable; not easily upset

data.chText: 她的心理状态不十分稳定。
data.enText: Mentally, she is not very stable.

data.chText: （化学状态或原子状态）稳定的
data.enText: staying in the same chemical or atomic state

data.chText: 化学状态稳定的
data.enText: chemically stable

data.chText: 马厩
data.enText: a building in which horses are kept
stables

data.chText: （养马作特定用途的）养马场；马房

data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的可数名词

data.enText: an organization that keeps horses for a particular purpose

data.chText: 骑用 / 赛马养马场
data.enText: a riding/racing stables

data.chText: 他的养马场在牛津附近。
data.enText: His stables are near Oxford.

data.chText: 统称某人拥有（或训练的）赛马
data.enText: a group of racehorses owned or trained by the same person

data.chText: 这个赛季他的马只有三匹获胜。
data.enText: There have been just three winners from his stable this season.

data.chText: （在同一地方工作或训练的）一批人；（同一公司生产的）系列产品
data.enText: a group of people who work or trained in the same place; a group of products made by the same company

data.chText: 同一剧团的几个男演员
data.enText: actors from the same stable

data.chText: 爱普生系列最新款式打印机
data.enText: the latest printer from the Epson stable

data.chText: 使（马）入厩；把（马）拴在马厩
data.enText: to put or keep a horse in a stable

data.chText: 你的矮种马养在哪儿？
data.enText: Where do you stable your pony?

simple_means.memory_skill: st 站，立 + able …的 → 能站住的 → 稳定的

means: (化学状态或原子状态)稳定的
统称某人拥有(或训练的)赛马

tr: a farm building for housing horses or other livestock
not taking part readily in chemical change
resistant to change of position or condition

value.def: If something is stable, it is not likely to change or come to an end suddenly.

example.ex: The price of oil should remain stable for the rest of 1992.
example.tran: 油价会在 1992 年剩下的时间里保持稳定。

example.ex: It was a time of political stability and progress.
example.tran: 这是一段政治稳定和进步的时期。

value.def: If someone has a stable personality, they are calm and reasonable and their mood does not change suddenly.

example.ex: Their characters are fully formed and they are both very stable children.
example.tran: 他们的性格已经完全形成，两人都是非常持重的孩子。

value.def: You can describe someone who is seriously ill as stable when their condition has stopped getting worse.

example.ex: The injured man was in a stable condition.

value.def: Chemical substances are described as stable when they tend to remain in the same chemical or atomic state.

example.ex: The less stable compounds were converted into a compound called Delta-A THC.
example.tran: 不太稳定的化合物被转换成了一种叫做Delta-A THC的化合物。

value.def: If an object is stable, it is firmly fixed in position and is not likely to move or fall.

example.tran: 这一结构必须得很稳固。

value.def: A stable or stables is a building in which horses are kept.
A stable or stables is an organization that breeds and trains horses for racing.

example.ex: Miss Curling won on two horses from Mick Trickey's stable.
example.tran: 柯林小姐在来自米克·特里齐养马场的两匹马身上下了注，结果她赢了。

value.def: When horses are stabled, they are put into a stable.

example.ex: The animals had been fed and stabled...
example.tran: 牲畜已经喂好并关进厩里了。

example.ex: You should allow your stabled horse a couple of hours' freedom per day.
example.tran: 你应该每天把关在马厩里的马放出来自由活动几个小时。

value.def: You can say that someone has a stable of people when they manage and promote the careers of that group of people.

example.ex: As chief executive, he assembled a polished stable of celebrities.
example.tran: 作为首席执行官，他手下云集了一批优雅的名人名士。

value.tran: 接受同一经纪人服务的一群人

value.def: If you say that someone has closed or shut the stable door after the horse has bolted, you mean that they have tried to prevent something happening but they have done so too late to prevent damage being done.

trans: 马厩式两截门(上下两部分可分别开关)
